Lets move TypeReference into method arguments:
    private <T> void assertResponse(final MvcResult mvcResult,
                                    final ResponseResult<T> expectedResult,
                                    final TypeReference<Result<T>> typeReference) throws Exception {
        final String actual = mvcResult.getResponse().getContentAsString();
        assertThat(actual).isNotBlank();
        assertThat(actual).isEqualToIgnoringWhitespace(getObjectMapper().writeValueAsString(expectedResult));

        final Result<T> actualResult = JsonMapper.parseData(actual, typeReference);
        assertEquals(expectedResult.getPayload(), actualResult.getPayload());
    }

Also, I would prefer to don't use isNotBlank method since it works incorrectly.
Could we use org.apache.commons.lang3.StringUtils#isNotBlank or org.skyscreamer.jsonassert.JSONAssert#assertEquals?

